{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 3, we illustrated that training α1-model with smart α1 initialization is difficult.",
    "For the optimization process, we used plain stochastic gradient descent (SGD) without a learning schedule and batch size 16.",
    "In Fig. 3a, the B1-model was trained with a learning rate equal to 0.0005, which is the same as in the corresponding ReLU network.",
    "For α1-model with smart α1 initialization the learning process with the same learning rate struggles to surpass a training accuracy of around 20%, confirming the presence of gradient instabilities.",
    "In this case, we found that decreasing to a very small learning rate of 0.00003 allowed to train the network."
  ]
}